* i2c introduction

developed by Philips


* i2c basics

- 2 wires 

. SDA: dataline
open drain and needs pull-up resistors

. SCLK: clockline

the master device generates the clock on the SCL line and 
initiates either a read or write operation.

after every 8 bits of data, the receiver sends an ACK or
NACK to indicate whether the transfer was successful.



* linux i2c subsystem

                I2C
                 |
                 |
       +---------+------------+
       |                      |
       |                      |
    DEVICE                  BUSES
       |                      |       
 +-----+-----+           +----+------+         
 |           |           |           |
 |           |           |           | 
DRIVER      CLIENT      ALGORITHMS ADAPTER


- Bus side
adaptor: represents the i2c controller hardware
algorith: defines how transfers are performed


- device side
client: represents a physical i2c slave device
driver: contains device-specific logi


